public interface ParentElementGetter<T extends ParentElementGetter<T>>
This interface is used for getting the parent object of an object. This interface also provides a method with a default implementation for getting the root object.

  • Method Details

    • getParent

      @Nullable T getParent()
      Gets the parent object of this object. If this object is already the root, then null is returned.
      Returns:
      The parent object of this object.

    • getRoot

      @NotNull default T getRoot()
      Gets the root object in the hierarchy it belongs to. If this object is already the root, then this object is returned.
      Returns:
      The root object of this element.

    • isRoot

      default boolean isRoot()
      Checks if this object is the root object in the hierarchy it belongs to.
      Returns:
      true if this object is the root object in the hierarchy it belongs to, false otherwise.
